`template/scripts/` is the set of static checks and sync tools shipped into every scaffolded project — CI gates that ctx-verify parses, plus the machinery that keeps those gates and the CTX binaries themselves current from an upstream CTX tooling repo.

All the check scripts (`cycle_check.sh`, `machete_check.sh`, `no_allow_check.sh`, `rationale_check.py`, `retired_terms_check.sh`, `workspace_lints_check.sh`) share one contract: enumerate files via `git ls-files -z --cached --others --exclude-standard`, never a filesystem walk, specifically to avoid racing concurrent `target/` writers; and emit failures as `FAIL: <path>:<line>: ...` lines with the location immediately after `FAIL:` (no other prefix), because ctx-verify's `split_loc` parser splits on the first colon+digit run. Any new check script must follow both conventions or ctx-verify silently misparses its output. `cycle_check.sh` is presently a stub (real cycle detection deferred to a dylint rule); `rationale_check.py` and the shell checks are the only ones doing real enforcement today.

`retired_terms_check.sh`'s `BANNED` array is the single source of truth for retired vocabulary — whenever an ADR retires a term, that array is the one place to update. `workspace_lints_check.sh` checks manifest shape only, not lint content.

The sync/build trio is a strict pipeline: `install-tools.sh` builds and copies `ctx-*` binaries from the upstream CTX repo (defaulting to `../CTX`, overridable via `$1`/`$CTX_REPO`); `update-template.sh` wraps it, additionally mirroring check scripts/configs/prompts and splicing the tool-contracts block into `CLAUDE.md`, syncing itself last since Bash can't safely overwrite a running multi-step script mid-execution. `gen_tool_contracts.sh` (invoked by `update-template.sh`) and `gen_readme_architecture.sh` both use the same `--write`/`--check` marker-splice shape and must keep their marker strings byte-identical to what the sync scripts grep for — changing one breaks the other silently. `gen_tool_contracts.sh` here is a known, intentional one-line divergence from its CTX-repo counterpart (`DOCS=(CLAUDE.md)` only); `update-template.sh` overwrites everything else in that file unconditionally, so any other diff is a bug.